[[File:Beaver Board advertisement, 1917.jpg|thumb|Advertisement for Beaver Board, 1917.]]
'''Beaverboard''' (also '''beaver board''') is a [[fiberboard]] building material, formed of [[wood fibre]] compressed into sheets. It was originally a [[trademark]].<ref>[http://www.answers.com/topic/beaverboard "beaverboard." ''The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language'', Fourth Edition. Houghton Mifflin Company, 2004. Answers.com 11 April 2008.]</ref> It has occasionally been used as a canvas by artists; most famously, the iconic painting ''[[American Gothic]]'' (1930) by [[Grant Wood]] is painted on a beaverboard panel.

